        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 3:57PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 357 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles southeast of Central Mills, or 16 miles northwest of Camden,
moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of north central
Wilcox County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
